generalCompliances.name: Accessibility
generalCompliances.description:
The Accessibility directive sets forth Cisco’s governing compliance with governmental laws and regulations and customer driven requirements for software and hardware products, and services, to be accessible to people with disabilities.  This directive applies to all Cisco products, from design to sale to post-sales support.
